    <sec sec-type="Introduction" id="SECID0ECH">
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <p>Wei, Zhang &amp; Zhou (2014) described the dolichopodid species <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Chrysotus</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">infirmus</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> from Guizhou Province, China. However, the scientific name was preoccupied by <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Chrysotus</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">infirmus</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Parent, 1933. Thus, the scientific name <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Chrysotus</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">infirmus</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Wei, Zhang &amp; Zhou, 2014 is a junior primary homonym of the species <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Chrysotus</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">infirmus</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Parent, 1933. According to Article 60.3 and 57.2 of the ICZN, the new replacement name <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Chrysotus</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">weii</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Zhou, <bold>nom. n.</bold> for <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Chrysotus</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">infirmus</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Wei, Zhang &amp; Zhou, 2014 is proposed.</p>
      <!--PageBreak-->
    </sec>
